	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I believe you can customize a few more things such as the size of icons when you view folders and such, but I doubt there is a simple quick solution to make one resolution simulate another... Because, you know, if you want a certain resolution you should use that instead of having another one simulate it.
<br />
<br />But of course, we're now in the LCD era where monitors have native resolutions and look like crap when using anything other than it, so I guess there isn't much you can do. Next time try the monitor before you buy it, to make sure you are comfortable with it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


